results.name: Number of partitions of n into parts 5k+2 and 5k+4 with at least one part of each type.
link: Robert Price, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
mathematica: nmax = 64;  s1 = Range[0, nmax/5]*5 + 2; s2 = Range[0, nmax/5]*5 + 4;
x_ /; ContainsAny[x, s1 ] && ContainsAny[x, s2 ]], {n, 1, nmax}] (* _Robert Price_, Aug 07 2020 *)
nmax = 64; l = Rest@CoefficientList[Series[(-1 + 1/Product[(1 - x^(5 k + 2)), {k, 0, nmax}])*(-1 + 1/Product[(1 - x^(5 k + 4)), {k, 0, nmax}]), {x, 0, nmax}], x]  (* _Robert Price_, Aug 16 2020 *)
